WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.390 --> 00:00:03.310
Now to build up the sections
of your master resume.

00:00:03.310 --> 00:00:05.980
These are the most commonly used
resume sections we've identified.

00:00:05.980 --> 00:00:09.450
A heading, which includes your name,
email, phone number, and

00:00:09.450 --> 00:00:12.320
links to any online profiles
including your LinkedIn, GitHub, and

00:00:12.320 --> 00:00:14.210
professional Twitter account.

00:00:14.210 --> 00:00:17.180
The skills section, which includes
your technical competencies and

00:00:17.180 --> 00:00:19.160
your level of expertise.

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:20.990
Use key words that
recruiters are looking for

00:00:20.990 --> 00:00:24.180
and give us a sync summary
of what you know how to do.

00:00:24.180 --> 00:00:28.130
Projects these are concrete examples
that illustrates your skills.

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:31.340
If they are in GitHub, the app store,
google play, or the web, your potential

00:00:31.340 --> 00:00:35.080
future employees can see the work
you've done in a very very literal way.

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:38.010
Relevant experience includes all
work history related to the job

00:00:38.010 --> 00:00:39.300
you're pursuing.

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:42.500
It should include details and
accomplishment and achievements.

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:45.655
Education is where you should list
any formal degree certificates and

00:00:45.655 --> 00:00:47.080
relevant courses.

00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:49.210
Be sure to include your
nano degree credentials.

00:00:50.260 --> 00:00:54.140
Awards, publications, presentations,
and interests are extra brownie points.

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:58.200
For example, you'll want to include
your publications for a research job.

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:01.460
If you're applying for sales, you might
mention sales achievements in the past.

00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:04.540
But those won't likely matter
as much for an engineering job.

00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:07.450
Of course you can include all
of those in your master resume.

00:01:07.450 --> 00:01:10.410
You'll be more selective when
devising your targeted resume.

00:01:10.410 --> 00:01:13.390
If you're looking to change careers,
a summary statement,

00:01:13.390 --> 00:01:16.345
projects, internships,
volunteer experience, and

00:01:16.345 --> 00:01:19.485
all the other amazing things you do in
your free time can be huge signifiers

00:01:19.485 --> 00:01:22.545
of a genuine interest in
the positions you're looking for.

00:01:22.545 --> 00:01:24.555
Have a category not mentioned here?

00:01:24.555 --> 00:01:26.035
Add your comments and
questions in the forum.

